This article is a press briefing by Press Secretary Jay Carney on March 15, 2011, regarding the response to the situation in Japan. Carney explains that the United States is doing everything it can to help Japan and its citizens affected by the tragic events. The US government is coordinating efforts to support Japan's response and has offered various forms of assistance, including disaster response experts, search and rescue teams, and technical advisors with nuclear expertise. The Nuclear Regulatory Commission and the State Department have issued updates on the situation at the nuclear plant in Japan and are urging American citizens to listen to local Japanese officials for the latest information. Carney also discusses other topics such as the situation in Bahrain and the ongoing discussions about a no-fly zone in Libya.